ame: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":25,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert FitzSauvin was born in 1190, in Glastonbury, Somerset, England, his father, Sauvinus De Turre, was 30 and his mother, Mrs Sauvinus De Turre, was 19. He had at least 1 son with Kathyrn de Brent. He died in 1219, in his hometown, at the age of 29."},"et":{"1190–1219":"1190–1219","1194–Female":"1194–Surnud","1220–1262":"1220–1262","1160–1193":"1160–1193","1172–Female":"1172–Surnud","1190":"1190","1215":"1215","1220":"1220","1262":"1262","1172":"1172","1194":"1194","1193":"1193","1160":"1160","1219":"1219","before 1190":"enne 1190","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England","Glastonbury, Somerset, England":"Glastonbury, Somerset, England"},"fi":{"1190–1219":"1190–1219","1194–Female":"1194–Kuollut","1220–1262":"1220–1262","1160–1193":"1160–1193","1172–Female":"1172–Kuollut","1190":"1190","1215":"1215","1220":"1220","1262":"1262","1172":"1172","1194":"1194","1193":"1193","1160":"1160","1219":"1219","before 1190":"ennen vuotta